name: Red Lobster closing 23 restaurants
summary: Red Lobster, a popular seafood restaurant chain, is closing 23 more of its locations, bringing the total number of shuttered restaurants to 129. The affected locations span across 15 states, including Alabama, California, Florida, Georgia, Illinois, Indiana, Iowa, Kansas, Kentucky, Michigan, Minnesota, Missouri, Ohio, Tennessee, and Virginia. The company has not disclosed the specific reasons for the closures, but the restaurant industry has been facing numerous challenges in recent years, such as rising costs, labor shortages, and changing consumer preferences. The closures will result in job losses for employees at the affected locations.

name: Zach Wilson
summary: The Denver Broncos' quarterback situation is in flux, with the team weighing its options between three candidates: Zach Wilson, Jarrett Stidham, and rookie Bo Nix. While Wilson was initially presumed to be the frontrunner for the starting role, Nix's recent performance in the preseason has put him in contention. Sean Payton, the Broncos' head coach, has stated that Wilson will make the 53-man roster, but his starting position is in doubt. Stidham is also expected to receive significant playing time, with Wilson getting the opportunity to prove himself as a backup option. Experts have suggested that the Broncos may ultimately make a "bold claim" regarding Wilson's status, while the New York Post reports that Wilson's future with the team is uncertain following the loss of the starting quarterback position to Nix.

summary: The Broncos will face the Cardinals in the third week of the NFL preseason. The game will be available live stream and on various channels. Secondly, running back Javonte Williams will make his preseason debut after recovering from a torn ACL. Finally, wide receiver Jerry Jeudy will look to build off his strong performance in the previous game.
